<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910423-0236</DOCNO><DOCID>910423-0236.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- 3Com Corp.:   Company Posts a Net Loss   Of $40.8 Million for Period</HL><DATE>03/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   COMS</CO><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   3Com Corp. said a restructuring charge of $67 millionresulted in a net loss of $40.8 million, or $1.46 a share,for the third quarter ended Feb. 28.   In the year-ago quarter, the Santa Clara, Calif., companyhad net income of $6.7 million, or 23 cents a share.</LP><TEXT>   Without the charge, which was $3 million less than thecompany projected in January, 3Com would have had net incomeof $2.3 million, or eight cents a share, the company said.   Sales fell 14% to $92.4 million from $107.3 million.   3Com is withdrawing from the network operating softwaresystems business and returning to its roots as a maker ofcomputer network hardware gear. As part of the restructuring,the company laid off 12% of its work force, a reduction ofabout 235 people.   For the nine months, 3Com reported a net loss of $31million, or $1.08 a share, compared with net income of $13.2million, or 45 cents a share, a year ago. Sales rose to$305.7 million from $302.3 million.</TEXT></DOC>